race.description: Roct Supports Tassie Racehorse Owners Hcp (Bm72)
race.comment: LOVIN' BEV (6) peaks and is knocking on the door. Has a high cruising speed and keeps the handy 2kg claim. Loves this course/distance and she's the leading contender. SH'BOURNE MIDNIGHT (3) resumes seeking the hat-trick. He performs fresh and brings a trial win from the track. Darmanin staying aboard suggests he's pleasing. THE SPIRIT OF ZERO (4) went close from the back at Hobart first-up and five winners have come out of that. Followed with a near miss on the synthetic. Finds a suitable race and can figure in the finish. VERBANO (9) is fitter for two runs back from a break. Turned in a better effort last time and gets in well this grade with the claim. Has ability and can run on into the finish.
